==English==

===Alternative forms===
* (UK) [[localise]]

===Etymology===
{{root|en|ine-pro|*stel-}}
From {{suffix|en|local|ize}}. Compare {{cog|fr|localiser}}.

===Verb===
{{en-verb}}

# {{lb|en|transitive}} To make [[local]]; to fix in, or [[assign]] to, a definite place.
#* {{quote-book|en|title=Memorials of a Tour in Italy|year=1837|section=Musings near Aquapendente|author=William Wordsworth|url=http://www.bartleby.com/145/ww881.html|passage=Out of her early struggles well inspired / To '''localize''' heroic acts}}
# {{lb|en|software|_|engineering}} To adapt a product for use in a particular country or region, typically by translating text into the language of that country and modifying currencies, date formats, etc.
#: ''We need to '''localize''' our software for the Japanese market.''
# To determine where something takes place or is to be found.

